      "message": "Fixing things up post-hoc seems a bit of a strange approach to me. ISTM that this is driven by the inadequate interface to literal.IndentTabs.\n\nIf I were to guess at a better approach, it would be to avoid invoking IndentTabs on the string literal parts of an interpolation, instead adding a bit more logic to the `ast.Interpolation` case inside `exprRaw`, doing the ParseQuotes there, and explicitly doing the string replace in each alternate basic lit (we know even-numbered elements must be string basic lits).\n\nThen we don\u0027t need to further clutter the state we maintain, which is hard to keep track of at the best of times.",
